 very identities ceaselessly evolve across from one life stage to another.Capturing the energy and excitement that Ovid’s poem generates among readers, Williams also sheds new light on its modern provocations. His fresh interpretations of the Metamorphoses reveal its power to enrich and inform our daily existence amid the uncertainties of life today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChange in literature. 0aFables, LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aLatin poetryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074967040uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/will2007040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231553759423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231553759/original  a978-3-11-074967-0  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK